HEADWORD: Cerite
<hw>Ce"rite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>ke`ras</grk>
horn.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A gastropod shell belonging to the
family <fam>Cerithi⟦ium⟧d⟦ae⟧</fam>; -- so called from its hornlike
form.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cerite</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Cerite
<hw>Ce"rite</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Cherium</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral of a brownish of cherry-red color,
commonly massive. It is a hydrous silicate of cerium and allied
metals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cerium</ent>⟦br⟧
